The ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException occurs in the Receipt class, specifically in the ActionListener for the 'modifierCommande' button. The problematic code is:

for (String historyEntry : historyList) {
    String[] splitEntry = historyEntry.split(" - Cout: ");
    previousHistory.put(splitEntry[0], Double.valueOf(splitEntry[1]));
}

If a historyEntry does not contain ' - Cout: ', splitEntry will have length 1, and accessing splitEntry[1] will throw an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException. To fix this, add a check to ensure the split result has length 2 before accessing splitEntry[1]:

for (String historyEntry : historyList) {
    String[] splitEntry = historyEntry.split(" - Cout: ");
    if (splitEntry.length == 2) {
        previousHistory.put(splitEntry[0], Double.valueOf(splitEntry[1]));
    }
}

This prevents the exception and only adds valid entries to previousHistory. The rest of the code remains unchanged, preserving all original functionality. The fix is minimal, easy to implement, and does not introduce new errors. 

